Hi again Anselm,

I have not used Heritrix 1.14, but I think you need to us=
e the Scripting Console in 3.2. You should be able to do both things you ar=
e asking about there. If you haven't found it already, this page has a lot =
of helpful scripts: https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/spaces/Heritrix/pages/=
7570099/Heritrix3+Useful+Scripts including one to "Delete URLs matching reg=
ex from frontier."


For searching crawl logs, I tend to search outside of =
the Heritrix interface at the commandline with grep -E. If you need to use =
the web interface, you can do it in the scripting console--I know you can r=
un arbitrary commands there (which can be dangerous so be careful what you =
run). But using the Groovy script engine, you could do something like:


ra=
wOut.println( "grep -E https://www.columbiamissourian.com/.*/gas.* jobs/mis=
souri/latest/logs/crawl.log".execute().text)


There are likely other ways =
to search the crawl log from the scripting console as well.


Lauren Ko
